file.name: threat_intelligence_exchange.yaml
file.content:
components:
  schemas:
    tmp0:
      properties:
        enterprise_reputation_num: {type: string}
        enterprise_reputation_str: {type: string}
        global_reputation_num: {type: string}
        global_reputation_str: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp1:
      properties:
        md5: {type: string}
        reputation_num: {type: string}
        reputation_str: {type: string}
        sha1: {type: string}
        sha256: {type: string}
        updated: {type: string}
      type: object
  securitySchemes: {}
info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of McAfee Threat Intelligence Exchange
  title: McAfee Threat Intelligence Exchange
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Lookup File Reputation on Threat Intelligence Exchange by MD5
      parameters:
      - description: MD5 hash to lookup in Threat Intelligence Exchange
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: MD5 Hash
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Threat Intelligence Exchange Lookup File Reputation
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Push MD5 hash and associated info to McAfee Threat Intelligence
        Exchange, can create new hash or update existing one.
      parameters:
      - description: MD5 hash to push to TIE
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: MD5 Hash
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: SHA1 hash to push to TIE
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: SHA1 Hash
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: SHA256 hash to push to TIE
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: SHA256 Hash
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'String Reputation level for associated MD5. One of the following:
          KNOWN_TRUSTED_INSTALLER, KNOWN_TRUSTED, MOST_LIKELY_TRUSTED, MIGHT_BE_TRUSTED,
          UNKNOWN, MIGHT_BE_MALICIOUS, MOST_LIKELY_MALICIOUS, KNOWN_MALICIOUS, NOT_SET'
        example: KNOWN_TRUSTED_INSTALLER
        in: query
        name: Reputation
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Filename to send into TIE Database
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Filename
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Comment for MD5 upload
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Comment
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: McAfee Threat Intelligence Exchange Push MD5
tags:
- {name: Investigation}
